SIMPLE: sunshiny
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sunshiny
<hw>Sun"shin`y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Bright
with the rays of the sun; clear, warm, or pleasant; <as>as, a
<ex>sunshiny</ex> day</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Bright like the sun; resplendent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Flashing beams of that <qex>sunshiny</qex> shield.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Beaming with good spirits; cheerful.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Her <xex>sunshiny</xex> face.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sunsquall</ent>⟦br⟧
